scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\post-processing-bloom.md:14:2. In the Inspector, navigate to **Add Override** &gt; **Post-processing**, and click on **Bloom**. Universal Render Pipeline applies **Bloom** to any Camera this Volume affects.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\particles-unlit-shader.md:3:Use this Shader for Particles that don’t need lighting. Because there are no time-consuming lighting calculations or lookups, this Shader is optimal for lower-end hardware. The Unlit Shader uses the most simple [shading model](shading-model.md) in the Universal Render Pipeline (URP).
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\particles-unlit-shader.md:10:2. Click __Shader__, and select __Universal Render Pipeline__ > __Particles__ > __Unlit__.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\particles-simple-lit-shader.md:3:In the Universal Render Pipeline (URP), use this Shader for particles where performance is more important than photorealism. This Shader uses a simple approximation for lighting. Because this Shader [does not calculate for physical correctness and energy conservation](shading-model.md#simple-shading), it renders quickly.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\particles-simple-lit-shader.md:10:2. Click __Shader__, and select __Universal Render Pipeline__ > __Particles__ > __Simple Lit__.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\particles-lit-shader.md:3:In the Universal Render Pipeline (URP), use this Shader to make particles appear almost photorealistic, for example for camp fire particles, rain drops or torch smoke. This Shader produces lifelike visuals but uses the most computationally heavy [shading model](shading-model.md) in URP, which can impact performance.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\particles-lit-shader.md:10:2. Click __Shader__, and select __Universal Render Pipeline__ > __Particles__ > __Lit__.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\package-samples.md:3:The Universal Render Pipeline (URP) comes with a set of samples to help you get started.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\package-sample-urp-package-samples.md:3:URP Package Samples is a [package sample](package-samples.md) for the Universal Render Pipeline (URP). It contains example shaders, C# scripts, and other assets you can build upon, use to learn how to use a feature, or use directly in your application. For information on how to import URP Package Samples into your project, refer to [Importing package samples](package-samples.md#importing-package-samples).
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\post-processing-vignette.md:12:2. In the Inspector, navigate to **Add Override** &gt; **Post-processing** and click on **Vignette**. Universal Render Pipeline applies **Vignette** to any Camera this Volume affects.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\post-processing-tonemapping.md:12:2. In the Inspector, navigate to **Add Override** &gt; **Post-processing**, and click on **Tonemapping**. The Universal Render Pipeline applies **Tonemapping** to any Camera this Volume affects.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\post-processing-ssao.md:5:URP implements the Screen Space Ambient Occlusion (SSAO) effect as a [Renderer Feature](urp-renderer-feature.md). It works with every shader that the Universal Render Pipeline (URP) provides as well as any custom opaque Shader Graphs you create.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\Post-Processing-Motion-Blur.md:5:Universal Render Pipeline (URP) only blurs camera motions.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\whats-new\urp-whats-new.md:146:You can now use the new [ScriptableRenderPass.Blit](https://docs.unity3d.com/Packages/com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.0/api/UnityEngine.Rendering.Universal.ScriptableRenderPass.html) method in your Scriptable Renderer Feature to apply effects to the color buffer without managing and handling Camera color buffers yourself. You can use the method to write effects that read and write to the Camera color buffer.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\Volumes.md:3:The Universal Render Pipeline (URP) uses the Volume framework. Volumes can override or extend Scene properties depending on the Camera position relative to each Volume.
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\use-built-in-shader-methods.md:3:The Universal Render Pipeline (URP) has a library of High-Level Shader Language (HLSL) shader files that contain helper methods. You can import these files into your custom shader files and use the helper methods.
