scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\shading-model.md:3:A shading model defines how a Material’s color varies depending on factors such as surface orientation, viewer direction, and lighting. Your choice of a shading model depends on the artistic direction and performance budget of your application. Universal Render Pipeline (URP) provides Shaders with the following shading models:
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\shaders-in-universalrp.md:30:The Universal Render Pipeline implements Physically Based Rendering (PBR).
scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Library\PackageCache\com.unity.render-pipelines.universal@12.1.15\Documentation~\shader-stripping.md:3:The shaders in the Universal Render Pipeline (URP) use [shader keywords](https://docs.unity3d.com/Manual/shader-keywords) to support many different features, which can mean Unity compiles a lot of [shader variants](https://docs.unity3d.com/Manual/shader-variants).
