# Changelog

All notable changes to DINOForge will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Fixed — SW building bundles now use URP Lit shader to prevent SRP batch crash
- **Switched procedural Star Wars building bundle material shader from Built-in `Standard` to URP `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit`** with fallback to `Universal Render Pipeline/Simple Lit` during assetbundle build, and switched tinting to `SetColor("_BaseColor", tint)` to keep `Hybrid Renderer V2` SRP batching compatibility.
- Rebuilt all 12 Star Wars building bundles on branch `feat/sw-building-bundles-20260531` using headless `Unity 2021.3.45f1` from `scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder` and confirmed the build log includes `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit`.

### Fixed — SW building stub bundles built real (#982)
- **12 remaining Star Wars BUILDING bundles were 90-byte stubs** — `sw-assembly-line`, `sw-blast-wall`, `sw-durasteel-barrier`, `sw-guard-tower`, `sw-heavy-foundry`, `sw-mining-facility`, `sw-processing-plant`, `sw-skyshield-generator`, `sw-tech-union-lab`, `sw-tibanna-refinery`, `sw-vulture-nest`, `sw-weapons-factory`. As placeholders they kept those buildings native in-game and made the swap engine (#986) re-load a useless stub every frame, flooding the AssetSwap log with "another AssetBundle with the same files is already loaded". Built REAL Unity 2021.3.45f1 AssetBundles for all 12 (each ~46-47 KB, up from 90 B) — distinct procedural SW-styled building silhouettes (factory / wall / tower / refinery / mine / lab / shield-emitter / vulture-nest / blast-barrier) on a faction-tinted Standard material (CIS grey / Republic white). New self-contained Editor builder `BuildSwBuildingBundles.cs` (meshes generated in-C# via `CombineInstance` of box primitives — no Blender / glTF dependency), promoted to `scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Editor/`. Built headless with the canonical `Unity.exe 2021.3.45f1` (`-batchmode -nographics -quit -executeMethod BuildSwBuildingBundles.Build`), exit 0, bundle headers verified `UnityFS ... 2021.3.45f1`. Bundle filename == `visual_asset` key == Addressable key; all 12 keys were already present in `addressables.yaml` / `asset_pipeline.yaml` (no CRC/hash fields, so no registration change needed). NOT deployed — deploy happens at reconcile.


